==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''[[PIN]] [[number]]''' (''plural'' '''PIN numbers''')

#A common alternative form of '''[[PIN]]''' (in the sense of "personal identification number").

====Usage notes====
*"PIN number" is a [[pleonasm]] as the "N" of "PIN" stands for "number".
*The use of "PIN number" rather than "PIN" is widespread but is avoided by careful speakers and writers.
*Some people may argue that "PIN number" is not redundant, as it avoids confusion with the word [[pin]].